Hemiedaphic springtails are commonly found in thick forest floors (Farska ́ and others 2013; Salmon and others 2014) and are therefore more likely to be affected by soil disturbance 
compared to epiedaphic species which can better tolerate disturbed and xeric habitats (Makkonen and others 2011; Bokhorst and others 2012; Rousseau and others 2019).

